rtedFeatureException: type is not available in this platform: com.oracle.svm.hosted.NativeImageSystemClassLoader\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.FutureTask.report(FutureTask.java:122)\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.FutureTask.get(FutureTask.java:191)\r\n        at com.oracle.graal.pointsto.util.AnalysisFuture.ensureDone(AnalysisFuture.java:64)\r\n```\n--- comments ---\nHi, nothing in that stacktrace involves ClassGraph code, so I don't know what to advise. However I believe that GraalVM code is first compiled into bytecodes, then converted into native code by the partial evaluator. You want to do your build-time scan between those two stages, and you don't want to include the scanner code in the bytecodes that are passed to the second stage. Unfortunately I have no idea exactly how to do that, so I would need your help to come up with a solution.\n---\nClosing due to lack of response -- please comment if you are able to help figure out how to get this working. (I don't use GraalVM so I don't know what to suggest.)\n---\n=== ISSUE 860 ===\nTrouble with GraalVM native-image post compile\nHello,\r\n\r\nI'm trying to build a project that uses ClassGraph into a GraalVM native-image.\r\n\r\nGraalVM does not handle reflection dynamically, so when code uses reflection, those references have to be explicitly stated in a json file so that Graal can make those connections during the compile phase.\r\n\r\nGraalVM also offers a handy tracer option that one can use where it monitors reflection use of your code as you run it and put it through its paces etc. where it automatically builds the necessary json files that you then include in your build statement when you compile the code.\r\n\r\nThe issue I'm running into seems to be with the way that ClassGraph does things so dynamically. My assumption is that there might be some nested dynamic reflection going on that the tracer tool can't catch and I'm not sure how to locate those so that I can add them in