ph/classgraph/issues/$id/comments?per_page=100\" | python3 -c 'import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); [print((x[\"body\"] or \"\")+\"\\n---\") for x in d]'\ndone", "timeout": 120}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_OatvDAPwiOBJ1WdTuB8Y3bb9|fc_02faa0ccd6450435016a5814e6568c8191af222ad717b1dc34", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "set -euo pipefail\ncurl -fsSL 'https://api.github.com/repos/classgraph/classgraph/commits?path=src/main/java/nonapi/io/github/classgraph/classpath/ClasspathFinder.java&until=2023-08-01T00%3A00%3A00Z&per_page=5' | python3 -c 'import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(x[\"sha\"][:10],x[\"commit\"][\"message\"].split(\"\\n\")[0]) for x in d]' || true\n# Print native-image-related 4.8.165 change notes by github commit search unauth could reject\ncurl -fsSL https://api.github.com/repos/classgraph/classgraph/releases/tags/classgraph-4.8.165 | python3 -c 'import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get(\"body\", \"\"))' || true", "timeout": 120}}], "api": "openai-codex-responses", "provider": "openai-codex", "model": "gpt-5.6-terra", "usage": {"input": 2837, "output": 435, "cacheRead": 56320, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59592, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1784157405053, "responseId": "resp_02faa0ccd6450435016a5814dd84e08191ba3cfc6cad2d9e85"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_69iZ7aEwoIB9HdjmFZf0jmqi|fc_02faa0ccd6450435016a5814e656788191b184f592228e7d29", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "=== ISSUE 750 ===\nSupport GraalVM native images\nWhen building a \"native\" application with classgraph `4.8.154`, using GraalVM `22.3` and `JDK 17`, the final generated image fails to run with the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\nException in thread \"main\" java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Method \"getLayer\" could not be invoked: java.lang.NoSuchMethodException: Could not find method java.lang.Module.getLayer\r\n\tat nonapi.io.github.classgraph.reflection.ReflectionUtils.invokeMethod(ReflectionUtils.java:231)\r\n\tat nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classpath.ModuleFinder.findModuleRefsFromCallstack(ModuleFinder.java:227)\r\n\tat nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classpath.ModuleFinder.<init>(ModuleFinder.java:284)\r\n\tat nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classpath.ClasspathFinder.<init>(ClasspathFinder.java:164)\r\n\tat io.github.classgraph.Scanner.<init>(Scanner.java:166)\r\n\tat io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scanAsync(ClassGraph.java:1531)\r\n\tat io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scanAsync(ClassGraph.java:1559)\r\n\tat io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scan(ClassGraph.java:1584)\r\n\tat io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scan(ClassGraph.java:1623)\r\n```\r\n\r\n...and...\r\n\r\n```\r\nCaused by: java.lang.RuntimeException: Could not find canHandle method for nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.AntClassLoaderHandler\r\n\tat nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry$ClassLoaderHandlerRegistryEntry.<init>(ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.java:163)\r\n\tat nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry$ClassLoaderHandlerRegistryEntry.<init>(ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.java:134)\r\n\tat nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.<clinit>(ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.java:47)\r\n\t... 14 more\r\nCaused by: java.lang.NoSuchMethodException: nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.AntClassLoaderHandler.canHandle(java.lang.Class, nonapi.io.github.classgraph.utils.LogNode)\r\n\tat java.base@17.0.5/java.lang.Class.getDeclaredMethod(DynamicHub.java:2675)\r\n\tat nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry$ClassLoaderHandlerRegistryEntry.<init>(ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.java:159)\r\n\t... 16 more\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn a Spring Boot/Spring world, fixing these would require something akin to the following:\r\n\r\n```java\r\npublic class MyRuntimeHints implements RuntimeHintsRegistrar {\r\n    public MyRuntimeHints() {\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    @Override\r\n    public void registerHints(final RuntimeHints hints, final ClassLoader classLoader) {\r\n        hints.reflection().registerType(java.lang.Module.class, MemberCategory.INVOKE_DECLARED_METHODS);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n...which in the end generates AOT JSON metadata for reflection as such:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n  {\r\n    \"name\": \"java.lang.Module\",\r\n    \"allDeclaredMethods\": true\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\n...and this would have to be repeated for `AntClassLoaderHandler`, and likely many others. \r\n\r\nThis JSON metadata is ideally found and provided by the project itself, so the AOT engine can just pick up up what it needs without having each consumer project declare and configure reflection metadata on their own. Alternatively, there is https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata which allows contributors to push this sort of configuration into a global repository that may be used by AOT engines and appropriate build plugins. \r\n\r\nBefore reaching out to graalvm-reachability-metadata, I figured to ask: Is this something classgraph might be open to supporting out of the box, whereby native-image configuration would be maintained and hosted here directly and then released? \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\n--- comments ---\nForgot to add that I am happy to help and assist however I can to move this effort along, should you be open to supporting it. I realize this is extra work, and likely something you may wish to punt, which is perfectly OK. Thank you!\n---\nHi, GraalVM native images do not have a concept of a classpath at runtime (just like Android, for similar reasons -- both are cross-compiled to a non-JVM runtime environment, and Graal additionally runs partial evaluation). There is really no way for ClassGraph to support runtime scanning in environments like this.\r\n\r\nHowever, there are some build-time scanning instructions here: https://github.com/classgraph/classgraph/wiki/Build-Time-Scanning\r\n\r\nThey may need updating. Please experiment with this to find the best solution for GraalVM, and let me know if you want to help improve these docs.\n---\nPS this is linked from the above wiki URL. https://github.com/SoftInstigate/classgraph-on-graalvm\n---\nThank you! Will do. \n---\nAny updates?\n---\n=== ISSUE 756 ===\nGraalVM native image failures during build-time scanning\nThis is actually a continuation of #681 which was closed.\r\n\r\nI was trying with ClassGraph `4.8.154` and encountered the same issue. I have set the appropriate `--initialize-at-build-time` arguments so that ClassGraph and my class performing the scan are initialized at build time.\r\n\r\nI referenced the project on https://github.com/SoftInstigate/classgraph-on-graalvm and found that this particular issue was introduced in `4.8.128`. The last version that worked on that project was `4.8.127`. https://github.com/classgraph/classgraph/compare/classgraph-4.8.127...classgraph-4.8.128.\r\n\r\nThis particular issue was introduced by the change to add a `ClassMemberCache`. This cache ends up being statically held because `ReflectionUtils` statically stores the `ReflectionDriver`.\r\nhttps://github.com/classgraph/classgraph/blob/dc3253595946048d2dbf4ce01e0b6333fa956b33/src/main/java/nonapi/io/github/classgraph/reflection/ReflectionUtils.java#L43\r\n\r\nI can get around this issue by setting the `reflectionDriver` to `null` after the scan has completed.\r\n\r\n```java\r\nnonapi.io.github.classgraph.reflection.ReflectionUtils.reflectionDriver = null;\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn my actual application I encountered another issue with the `CallStackReader` statically storing `callStack`.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/classgraph/classgraph/blob/8b358c63db2b4a5dc844f96e9453809b8f83adf8/src/main/java/nonapi/io/github/classgraph/classpath/CallStackReader.java#L45\r\n\r\nI had to use reflection to clear this out after the scan has completed for the image building process to complete successfully.\r\n\r\n```java\r\ntry {\r\n\tClass<?> clazz = Class.forName(\"nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classpath.CallStackReader\");\r\n\tField field = clazz.getDeclaredField(\"callStack\");\r\n\tfield.setAccessible(true);\r\n\tfield.set(null, null);\r\n} catch (ClassNotFoundException | NoSuchFieldException | SecurityException | IllegalArgumentException\r\n\t\t| IllegalAccessException e) {\r\n\tthrow new RuntimeException(e);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nI will try to find time to create a small test case project that demonstrates this.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\n--- comments ---\nThanks for the detailed report. I included code to fix both cases.\r\n\r\nNote that to clear the `reflectionDriver` reference, you need to call `ScanResult#close()` when the scan is complete (i.e. scan in `try-catch` as recommended in the docs).\r\n\r\nReleased in 4.8.155.\n---\nThanks for the quick response! It's now fixed.\n---\nYou're welcome :) \n---\n=== ISSUE 681 ===\nFailed to build-time scan on graalvm native image\nthe example from `https://github.com/SoftInstigate/classgraph-on-graalvm`  does not apply\r\n\r\n```\r\n[1/7] Initializing...                                                                                    (3.4s @ 0.18GB)\r\n Version info: 'GraalVM 22.1.0 Java 17 CE'\r\n C compiler: cl.exe (microsoft, x64, 19.29.30133)\r\n Garbage collector: Serial GC\r\n[2/7] Performing analysis...  [*]                                                                        (5.1s @ 0.79GB)\r\n   3,414 (76.94%) of  4,437 classes reachable\r\n   4,295 (51.79%) of  8,293 fields reachable\r\n  15,361 (45.62%) of 33,669 methods reachable\r\n     119 classes,    44 fields, and   277 methods registered for reflection\r\n\r\nError: java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException: com.oracle.graal.pointsto.constraints.UnsupportedFeatureException: type is not available in this platform: com.oracle.svm.hosted.NativeImageSystemClassLoader\r\ncom.oracle.graal.pointsto.util.AnalysisError: java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException: com.oracle.graal.pointsto.constraints.UnsupportedFeatureException: type is not available in this platform: com.oracle.svm.hosted.NativeImageSystemClassLoader\r\n        at com.oracle.graal.pointsto.util.AnalysisError.shouldNotReachHere(AnalysisError.java:172)\r\n        at com.oracle.graal.pointsto.util.AnalysisFuture.ensureDone(AnalysisFuture.java:66)\r\n        at com.oracle.graal.pointsto.heap.ImageHeapScanner.lambda$postTask$9(ImageHeapScanner.java:611)\r\n        at com.oracle.graal.pointsto.util.CompletionExecutor.executeCommand(CompletionExecutor.java:193)\r\n        at com.oracle.graal.pointsto.util.CompletionExecutor.lambda$executeService$0(CompletionExecutor.java:177)\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinTask$RunnableExecuteAction.exec(ForkJoinTask.java:1395)\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinTask.doExec(ForkJoinTask.java:373)\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool$WorkQueue.topLevelExec(ForkJoinPool.java:1182)\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.scan(ForkJoinPool.java:1655)\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.runWorker(ForkJoinPool.java:1622)\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinWorkerThread.run(ForkJoinWorkerThread.java:165)\r\nCaused by: java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException: com.oracle.graal.pointsto.constraints.UnsupportedFeatureException: type is not available in this platform: com.oracle.svm.hosted.NativeImageSystemClassLoader\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.FutureTask.report(FutureTask.java:122)\r\n        at java.base/java.util.concurrent.FutureTask.get(FutureTask.java:191)\r\n        at com.oracle.graal.pointsto.util.AnalysisFuture.ensureDone(AnalysisFuture.java:64)\r\n```\n--- comments ---\nHi, nothing in that stacktrace involves ClassGraph code, so I don't know what to advise. However I believe that GraalVM code is first compiled into bytecodes, then converted into native code by the partial evaluator. You want to do your build-time scan between those two stages, and you don't want to include the scanner code in the bytecodes that are passed to the second stage. Unfortunately I have no idea exactly how to do that, so I would need your help to come up with a solution.\n---\nClosing due to lack of response -- please comment if you are able to help figure out how to get this working. (I don't use GraalVM so I don't know what to suggest.)\n---\n=== ISSUE 860 ===\nTrouble with GraalVM native-image post compile\nHello,\r\n\r\nI'm trying to build a project that uses ClassGraph into a GraalVM native-image.\r\n\r\nGraalVM does not handle reflection dynamically, so when code uses reflection, those references have to be explicitly stated in a json file so that Graal can make those connections during the compile phase.\r\n\r\nGraalVM also offers a handy tracer option that one can use where it monitors reflection use of your code as you run it and put it through its paces etc. where it automatically builds the necessary json files that you then include in your build statement when you compile the code.\r\n\r\nThe issue I'm running into seems to be with the way that ClassGraph does things so dynamically. My assumption is that there might be some nested dynamic reflection going on that the tracer tool can't catch and I'm not sure how to locate those so that I can add them into the proper json file.\r\n\r\nHere is the stack trace that comes out of the native image once it's compiled:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nException in Application start method\r\nException in thread \"main\" java.lang.RuntimeException: Exception in Application start method\r\n        at javafx.graphics@22.0.1/com.sun.javafx.application.LauncherImpl.launchApplication1(LauncherImpl.java:893)\r\n        at javafx.graphics@22.0.1/com.sun.javafx.application.LauncherImpl.lambda$launchApplication$2(LauncherImpl.java:196)\r\n        at java.base@22.0.1/java.lang.Thread.runWith(Thread.java:1583)\r\n        at java.base@22.0.1/java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:1570)\r\n        at org.graalvm.nativeimage.builder/com.oracle.svm.core.thread.PlatformThreads.threadStartRoutine(PlatformThreads.java:858)\r\n        at org.graalvm.nativeimage.builder/com.oracle.svm.core.thread.PlatformThreads.threadStartRoutine(PlatformThreads.java:834)\r\nCaused by: java.lang.ExceptionInInitializerError\r\n        at SimpleOTP@1.0/com.simtechdata.simpleotp.database.DB.<clinit>(DB.java:27)\r\n        at SimpleOTP@1.0/com.simtechdata.simpleotp.Main.tryDatabase(Main.java:153)\r\n        at SimpleOTP@1.0/com.simtechdata.simpleotp.Main.start(Main.java:125)\r\n        at javafx.graphics@22.0.1/com.sun.javafx.application.LauncherImpl.lambda$launchApplication1$9(LauncherImpl.java:839)\r\n        at javafx.graphics@22.0.1/com.sun.javafx.application.PlatformImpl.lambda$runAndWait$12(PlatformImpl.java:483)\r\n        at javafx.graphics@22.0.1/com.sun.javafx.application.PlatformImpl.lambda$runLater$10(PlatformImpl.java:456)\r\n        at java.base@22.0.1/java.security.AccessController.executePrivileged(AccessController.java:128)\r\n        at java.base@22.0.1/java.security.AccessController.doPrivileged(AccessController.java:400)\r\n        at javafx.graphics@22.0.1/com.sun.javafx.application.PlatformImpl.lambda$runLater$11(PlatformImpl.java:455)\r\n        at javafx.graphics@22.0.1/com.sun.glass.ui.InvokeLaterDispatcher$Future.run(InvokeLaterDispatcher.java:95)\r\nCaused by: io.github.classgraph.ClassGraphException: Uncaught exception during scan\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scan(ClassGraph.java:1637)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scan(ClassGraph.java:1654)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scan(ClassGraph.java:1667)\r\n        at SimpleOTP@1.0/com.simtechdata.simpleotp.resources.Resources.<init>(Resources.java:39)\r\n        at SimpleOTP@1.0/com.simtechdata.simpleotp.resources.Resources.<clinit>(Resources.java:30)\r\n        ... 10 more\r\nCaused by: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Method \"list\" could not be invoked: java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/nonapi.io.github.classgraph.reflection.ReflectionUtils.invokeMethod(ReflectionUtils.java:231)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/io.github.classgraph.ModuleReaderProxy.list(ModuleReaderProxy.java:110)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/io.github.classgraph.ClasspathElementModule.scanPaths(ClasspathElementModule.java:304)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/io.github.classgraph.Scanner$4.processWorkUnit(Scanner.java:1097)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/io.github.classgraph.Scanner$4.processWorkUnit(Scanner.java:1091)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/nonapi.io.github.classgraph.concurrency.WorkQueue.runWorkLoop(WorkQueue.java:246)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/nonapi.io.github.classgraph.concurrency.WorkQueue.access$000(WorkQueue.java:50)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/nonapi.io.github.classgraph.concurrency.WorkQueue$1.call(WorkQueue.java:201)\r\n        at io.github.classgraph/nonapi.io.github.classgraph.concurrency.WorkQueue$1.call(WorkQueue.java:198)\r\n        at java.base@22.0.1/java.util.concurrent.FutureTask.run(FutureTask.java:317)\r\n        at java.base@22.0.1/java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor.runWorker(ThreadPoolExecutor.java:1144)\r\n        at java.base@22.0.1/java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker.run(ThreadPoolExecutor.java:642)\r\n        at java.base@22.0.1/java.lang.Thread.runWith(Thread.java:1583)\r\n        at java.base@22.0.1/java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:1570)\r\n        at org.graalvm.nativeimage.builder/com.oracle.svm.core.thread.PlatformThreads.threadStartRoutine(PlatformThreads.java:858)\r\n        at org.graalvm.nativeimage.builder/com.oracle.svm.core.thread.PlatformThreads.threadStartRoutine(PlatformThreads.java:834)\r\n```\r\n\r\nBased on another issue that I saw here related to GraalVM, I think we are both kind of treading on uncharted waters so to speak. So I'm starting this issue with hopes that together, we can figure out how to properly compile a java project into a native-image when ClassGraph is used in the project.\r\n\r\nMy project is modular by the way and I'm using Java 22.\r\n\r\nI am able to run the project from its compiled jar file without any issue it's only after compiling it into a native-image do I run into this issue.\r\n\r\nThanks.\n--- comments ---\nHi, I'm a huge fan of GraalVM's usage of partial evaluation (Futamura projections) for cross-platform compilation, but I have never tried to use it for anything serious, so I really don't know anything about this.\r\n\r\nBy the looks of things though, the Graal runtime does not compile the Java module system into the final binary (it may just resolve modules and classes at compiletime), and/or has limitations on reflection, as you point out.\r\n\r\nThe reason ClassGraph uses reflection to call `ModuleReader` (via `ModuleReaderProxy`) is that ClassGraph is built for JDK 7, for maximum compatibility. I have considered raising the minimum JDK version to 11 or even 17 for ClassGraph 5.0 (although I don't have time to work on that right now). But part of that change could be to drop `ModuleReaderProxy` and just use `ModuleReader` (which was introduced in JDK 9) directly.\r\n\r\nWhat I wrote in the docs is that to support Java environments that are non-standard (like Android, or GraalVM), you should do your scanning at build-time:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/classgraph/classgraph/wiki/Build-Time-Scanning\n---\n@lukehutch \r\n\r\nI tried serializing everything at build time then added the json file into my resources folder, then built the ScanResult from the json file, but I get the same results.\r\n\r\nI'm using ClassGraph mainly for the convenience of getting at the files in the resources folder. It's been handy for this project where those files change a lot, ClassGraph lets me not have to worry about tracking the files explicitly in the program.\r\n\r\nI may need to just go back to Javas built in means of getting at those files. Graal seems to handle that method pretty well.\n---\nOK, well if you can add the resource files to the traditional classpath, rather than to the module path, then you can disable module scanning, and ClassGraph should work for you again.\n---\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1784157417359}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_OatvDAPwiOBJ1WdTuB8Y3bb9|fc_02faa0ccd6450435016a5814e6568c8191af222ad717b1dc34", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2bb319215c Make ReflectionUtils non-static (#756, #757)\n955baf59b9 Release static references after scan is complete (#756)\ndf45ffa6cc Also scan classpath if override classloader is AppClassLoader (#639)\naff50c4ab3 A few tweaks to PR #592\n718bcba85c ModuleFinder understands which modules the user requested\nAdd module dependencies in manifest file for JBoss (#808, thanks to @redmitry for reporting).\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1784157417359}]}
